a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"WPML versions\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://wpml.org/?p=1127313\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:349:\"{Updated Post on 6/12/16} WPML 3.6.1 is now released and it applies the configuration to Divi and Visual Composer automatically. No need anymore to install any XML configuration files manually. WPML 3.6.0 is now available in first beta. The major new feature of this release is convenient translation for sites built with page builders. In [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Amir\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11597:\"<p><strong> {Updated Post on 6/12/16} WPML 3.6.1 is now released and it applies the configuration to Divi and Visual Composer automatically. No need anymore to install any XML configuration files manually.</strong></p>\n<p>WPML 3.6.0 is now available in first beta. The major new feature of this release is convenient translation for sites built with page builders. In this beta you can experiment with Divi and Visual Composer.</p>\n<p>Until today, in order to translate sites that are built with page builders, you had to rebuild each page, with the page builder, in each language. This works fine for small sites that have few languages. It&#8217;s more challenging for busy sites that have a lot of content and many languages. And, it was a showstopper for anyone wanting to work with translators.</p>\n<p>WPML 3.6.0 changes all this. Now, when you design content with a page builder, you will have the option to conveniently translate only the texts, without going into the builder to translate (it&#8217;s a new option. You can still translate &#8220;the old way&#8221;, by designing with the page builder each language separately). The same workflow will work if you&#8217;re translating yourself, sending content to your own translators or using a translation service.</p>\n<p>Let&#8217;s see how it works.</p>\n<h2>Install WPML Translation Management, String Translation and Configure WPML</h2>\n<p>First, you need to install both <strong>Translation Management</strong> and <strong>String Translation</strong>. Both are available from your <a href=\"https://wpml.org/account/\">WPML account</a>, if you have a <strong>Multilingual CMS</strong> account. If you have a <strong>Multilingual Blog</strong> account, you can upgrade and pay only the difference.</p>\n<p>Next, go to <strong>WPML-&gt;Translation Management-&#038;Multilingual Content Setup</strong> and select to <strong>Use the translation editor</strong>.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_1127319\" style=\"width: 310px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/use-translation-editor.jpg\"><img src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/use-translation-editor-300x148.jpg\" alt=\"Enable using the Translation Editor\" width=\"300\" height=\"148\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-1127319\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/use-translation-editor-300x148.jpg 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/use-translation-editor-150x74.jpg 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/use-translation-editor-768x380.jpg 768w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/use-translation-editor.jpg 855w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Enable using the Translation Editor</p></div>\n<p><strong><sup>*</sup> The production version of WPML 3.6.0 will help you with this step. It will detect when WPML components are missing, suggest to install them for you and set the translation method correctly.</strong></p>\n<h2>Tell WPML How to Translate the Page Builder</h2>\n<p><strong><sup>*</sup> This techie step is not required anymore, it was only required for WPML 3.6.0 beta.</strong></p>\n<h2>Design with the Page Builder</h2>\n<p>Here is a sample page that we&#8217;ve designed with Visual Composer:</p>\n<table>\n<tr>\n<td><div id=\"attachment_1128039\" style=\"width: 310px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/front-end-divi-page.jpg\"><img src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/front-end-divi-page-300x291.jpg\" alt=\"Page designed with Divi 3\" width=\"300\" height=\"291\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-1128039\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/front-end-divi-page-300x291.jpg 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/front-end-divi-page-150x145.jpg 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/front-end-divi-page-768x744.jpg 768w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/front-end-divi-page.jpg 844w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Page designed with Divi 3</p></div></td>\n<td>\n<div id=\"attachment_1127402\" style=\"width: 310px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/page-with-visual-composer.jpg\"><img src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/page-with-visual-composer-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"Page designed with Visual Composer\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-1127402\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/page-with-visual-composer-300x225.jpg 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/page-with-visual-composer-150x112.jpg 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/page-with-visual-composer-768x575.jpg 768w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/page-with-visual-composer.jpg 1010w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Page designed with Visual Composer</p></div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<p>(I&#8217;ll be the first to admit that we could have designed something nicer.)</p>\n<p>You can see the + icons for adding translations to the page.</p>\n<h2>Translate with WPML&#8217;s Translation Editor</h2>\n<p>I click to add translation to Spanish and I arrive at WPML&#8217;s Translation Editor (this is what we&#8217;ve configured WPML to do in the first step).</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_1127404\" style=\"width: 306px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/vc-translation-tm.jpg\"><img src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/vc-translation-tm-296x300.jpg\" alt=\"Translating the sample page\" width=\"296\" height=\"300\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-1127404\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/vc-translation-tm-296x300.jpg 296w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/vc-translation-tm-148x150.jpg 148w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/vc-translation-tm-768x779.jpg 768w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/vc-translation-tm-90x90.jpg 90w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/vc-translation-tm.jpg 1005w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 296px) 100vw, 296px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Translating the sample page</p></div>\n<p>You can see that the translation editor includes fields for translation. There&#8217;s a field for the page title and then fields for each of the cells in the page builder. Only cells that have text will appear. This means that the translator working on the page doesn&#8217;t need to worry about the design. Translators now only need to translate and only need to translate texts. There are no shortcodes in the text and nothing else to make the translator&#8217;s work difficult.</p>\n<p>I&#8217;m translating all the fields, click on &#8220;translation complete&#8221; next to each and then &#8220;save and close&#8221; the translation editor.</p>\n<p>When I get back to the translated page, the + icon will change to a pencil. This tells us that it&#8217;s translated already and now I can edit it.</p>\n<h2>Check the Results</h2>\n<p>We&#8217;re all done. Let&#8217;s look at the page on the front-end, in English and in Spanish.</p>\n<table>\n<tr>\n<th>English (original)</th>\n<th>Spanish (translated)</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/front-end-vc-page-narrow.jpg\"><img src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/front-end-vc-page-narrow-298x300.jpg\" alt=\"front-end-vc-page-narrow\" width=\"298\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-1128047\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/front-end-vc-page-narrow-298x300.jpg 298w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/front-end-vc-page-narrow-150x150.jpg 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/front-end-vc-page-narrow-768x773.jpg 768w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/front-end-vc-page-narrow-90x90.jpg 90w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/front-end-vc-page-narrow.jpg 790w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 298px) 100vw, 298px\" /></a></td>\n<td><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/es-front-end-vc-page-narrow.jpg\"><img src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/es-front-end-vc-page-narrow-287x300.jpg\" alt=\"es-front-end-vc-page-narrow\" width=\"287\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-1128048\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/es-front-end-vc-page-narrow-287x300.jpg 287w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/es-front-end-vc-page-narrow-144x150.jpg 144w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/es-front-end-vc-page-narrow-768x802.jpg 768w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/es-front-end-vc-page-narrow.jpg 790w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 287px) 100vw, 287px\" /></a></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<p>And, remember, we only designed this page ONCE using the builder.</p>\n<h2>Summary of the Translation Process</h2>\n<p>This blog post is a little long and includes a lot of details because it&#8217;s a beta version. The usage instructions for the production version will be a lot simpler:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Design with your page builder</li>\n<li>Translate</li>\n</ol>\n<p>There&#8217;s a bit of preparation work here because this beta version still doesn&#8217;t do all the automation of the production version. If you need help with any of the steps, please let us know.</p>\n<h2>Download and Try</h2>\n<p>WPML 3.6.0 is available as beta. To get it, log in to your <a href=\"https://wpml.org/account/\">WPML account</a>, click on Downloads and scroll to the bottom. You will see <strong>CMS Beta Package</strong>. Download and extract it. Inside, there are ZIP files for all of WPML&#8217;s components. To use a beta, you need to use all of WPML&#8217;s components from that package and not mix with production versions.</p>\n<p>This is a beta, so you should only use it on development sites.</p>\n<p>WPML 3.6.0 is going into QA next week. We will probably release more betas and we&#8217;re planning to have the production version in about a month. The production version of WPML will also include the <a href=\"https://wpml.org/2016/09/want-try-new-language-switcher-coming-wpml/\">new language switcher</a>, more improvements, some fixes and full compatibility with WordPress 4.7.</p>\n<div class=\"feedflare\">\n<a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=Gh85wFiAHhQ:WCnqXYgJVrs:D7DqB2pKExk\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=Gh85wFiAHhQ:WCnqXYgJVrs:D7DqB2pKExk\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=Gh85wFiAHhQ:WCnqXYgJVrs:gIN9vFwOqvQ\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=Gh85wFiAHhQ:WCnqXYgJVrs:gIN9vFwOqvQ\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=Gh85wFiAHhQ:WCnqXYgJVrs:V_sGLiPBpWU\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=Gh85wFiAHhQ:WCnqXYgJVrs:V_sGLiPBpWU\" border=\"0\"></img></a>\n</div><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wpml/~4/Gh85wFiAHhQ\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:88:\"https://wpml.org/2016/11/wpml-3-6-0-beta-with-translation-for-divi-visual-composer/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2:\"64\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:83:\"https://wpml.org/2016/11/wpml-3-6-0-beta-with-translation-for-divi-visual-composer/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:46:\"Are you all set with WooCommerce Multilingual?\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpml/~3/odgLymtzeYA/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:67:\"https://wpml.org/2016/10/all-set-woocommerce-multilingual/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 27 Oct 2016 08:24:22 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Compatibility\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://wpml.org/?p=1122473\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:349:\"WooCommerce is now the de-facto standard for e-commerce sites for WordPress. In fact, it&#8217;s the single most used software for e-commerce on the Web. We want to make sure that you have everything needed from WPML, to successfully run multilingual WooCommerce sites. A year ago, we ran a survey about your needs from multilingual sites. [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Amir\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6232:\"<p><strong>WooCommerce is now the de-facto standard for e-commerce sites for WordPress. In fact, it&#8217;s the single most used software for e-commerce on the Web. We want to make sure that you have everything needed from WPML, to successfully run multilingual WooCommerce sites.</strong></p>\n<p>A year ago, we ran a survey about your needs from multilingual sites.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_1122509\" style=\"width: 310px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/status-multilingual-woocommerce-2015.jpg\"><img src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/status-multilingual-woocommerce-2015-300x251.jpg\" alt=\"Status of WooCommerce Multilingual in 2015\" width=\"300\" height=\"251\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-1122509\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/status-multilingual-woocommerce-2015-300x251.jpg 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/status-multilingual-woocommerce-2015-150x126.jpg 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/status-multilingual-woocommerce-2015.jpg 671w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Status of WooCommerce Multilingual in 2015</p></div>\n<p>While 42% of the people replied that they are all set, 45% had some small issues and 12% reported serious problems. Our goal was to fix it for everyone.</p>\n<p>A detailed study of all reported problems shows that you were short on features, compatibility and performance (in that order). </p>\n<div id=\"attachment_1122517\" style=\"width: 310px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/wcml-issues-breakdown-2015.jpg\"><img src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/wcml-issues-breakdown-2015-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"Breakdown of issues with multilingual WooCommerce, 2015\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-1122517\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/wcml-issues-breakdown-2015-300x200.jpg 300w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/wcml-issues-breakdown-2015-150x100.jpg 150w, https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/wcml-issues-breakdown-2015.jpg 671w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Breakdown of issues with multilingual WooCommerce, 2015</p></div>\n<p>Most of the requested features were actually compatibility issues with various WooCommerce extensions.</p>\n<p>During 2016, we did several rounds of compatibility and performance improvements. We also ran three usability tests to uncover usability issues. Turns out that many of the features that people requested were already implemented, but hard to find.</p>\n<p>A lot of the work on compatibility went into the big extensions, which many WooCommerce sites use. You can find detailed how-to manuals on:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://wpml.org/documentation/woocommerce-extensions-compatibility/translating-woocommerce-tab-manager-woocommerce-multilingual/\">Translating WooCommerce Tab Manager</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://wpml.org/documentation/woocommerce-extensions-compatibility/translating-woocommerce-subscriptions-woocommerce-multilingual/\">Translating WooCommerce Subscriptions</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://wpml.org/documentation/woocommerce-extensions-compatibility/translating-woocommerce-product-add-ons-woocommerce-multilingual/\">Translating WooCommerce Product Add-Ons</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://wpml.org/documentation/woocommerce-extensions-compatibility/translating-woocommerce-bookings-woocommerce-multilingual/\">Translating WooCommerce Bookings</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://wpml.org/documentation/woocommerce-extensions-compatibility/translating-woocommerce-table-rate-shipping-woocommerce-multilingual/\">Translating WooCommerce Table Rate Shipping</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>As a result, WooCommerce Multilingual now comes with an improved setup wizard, is fully compatible with leading WooCommerce extensions and overall allows running multilingual WooCommerce sites much more efficiently.</p>\n<p>You can probably imagine how happy we are with ourselves right now <img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/2.2.1/72x72/1f642.png\" alt=\"🙂\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /></p>\n<p>Going forward, we want to make sure that we focus our efforts on what you need. You can imagine that we are getting a lot of feature requests and suggestions. You can help us prioritize by leaving your comments. Tell us how <a href=\"https://wpml.org/documentation/related-projects/woocommerce-multilingual/\">WooCommerce Multilingual</a> is working for you, if you&#8217;re running into any problems and what else you need for your current and upcoming projects.</p>\n<p>If you are reporting a technical issue, best to first report (in detail) in our <a href=\"https://wpml.org/forums/forum/english-support/\">technical support forum</a>. Then, leave a comment here with a brief description and the link to the forum thread.</p>\n<p>And, we would love to get your support. If you&#8217;re happy with WooCommerce Multilingual, show your support by giving us a good rating on the <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/woocommerce-multilingual/\">WordPress download page</a>. Every vote counts and every good rating helps us. With your rating, we get other authors more engaged and active in compatibility with WPML.</p>\n<div class=\"feedflare\">\n<a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=odgLymtzeYA:K_Nyzjrs63A:D7DqB2pKExk